@startuml object_input_to_fcam_camera_state_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Object Input To FCAM Camera State Signal Flow\n(object/nav/path context -> FCAM camera health and detection publish)

participant "Object / NAV /\npath context" as CameraCtx #F4F7FB
participant "FCAM\ncamera state owner" as FCAM #E8F7E8
participant "Camera state bus" as CameraBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / pilot users" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Camera Inputs ==

CameraCtx -> FCAM : objectTrackValid\nobjectConfidence\nnavRouteClass\nobjectInputStale\nnavInputStale\npathReady
FCAM -> FCAM : if objectInputStale then\ntrack = 0 / confidence = 0
FCAM -> FCAM : if pathReady == 0\nthen navRouteClass = 0
FCAM -> FCAM : objectDetected = clamp(objectTrackValid, 0, 1)
FCAM -> FCAM : laneModelValid = calcLaneModelValid(navRouteClass, navInputStale, pathReady)
FCAM -> FCAM : cameraHealth =\n0 if pathReady == 0 or objectInputStale\n1 if navInputStale\n2 otherwise
note right of FCAM
Representative gating inputs
- objectTrackValid / objectConfidence
- navRouteClass
- objectInputStale / navInputStale
- pathReady
end note

== Camera Publish ==

FCAM -> CameraBus : frmFcamInputMsg\nCameraHealth / ObjectDetected / LaneModelValid / Confidence
note right of FCAM
Representative outputs
- CameraHealth
- ObjectDetected
- LaneModelValid
- Confidence
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

CameraBus -> Obs : camera-state readback /\nhighway-pilot consumers

note over CameraCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Object, NAV, and path context reach FCAM
2. FCAM normalizes stale and no-path conditions
3. FCAM publishes camera health, detection, and lane-model status
4. Pilot users and observers consume the effective camera state
end note

@enduml
